#: ../../_includes/_adminpanel/mta.rst:145
msgid "*Pipelining* is formally defined in :rfc:`2920` and refers to the ability of an SMTP server to process multiple commands send by a connecting client, as opposed as the standard process in which the client must wait for a reply or answer from the server before being allowed to send another command. Enabling this option is resource-consuming, because a client that passes this test is required to disconnect and reconnect to be able to communicate with the SMTP server."
