msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:180
msgid "A :term:`Meeting` is a video call between two :term:`Participants <Participant>`, while a Group Meeting is a meeting between three or more Participants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:184
msgid "Members vs. Participants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:186
msgid "A Group is composed by three of more users, which are the *members* of the Group: all members receive the text messages written in the chat. Whenever a Group Meeting is started, while all the members can join that Group Meeting, only those who indeed take part are called *participants*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:192
msgid "To take part to a meeting, use the button on the top right of the chat window: if you are starting the meeting, the button is called :bdg-light:`START MEETING`, while if the meeting has already started (in the case of a video conference), the button becomes :bdg-light:`JOIN MEETING`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:198
msgid "If someone is trying to call you directly, a dialog allows you to accept the call and enter the meeting or to refuse the call and write a short message that will be sent to the caller. Upon entering the meeting, you have the chance to choose the microphone and webcam (i.e., the *devices*) to use and to test the microphone. The selected devices are always shown, to make clear which are the one used when entering the call. You can also start a call with both devices deactivated and enable them during the call, and even change them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:207
msgid "After the meeting has started, on the left-hand side three collapsible panels appear: the *Actions* and *Participant* boxes, which are the same as the corresponding *Actions* and *Members* box in the textual chat, and the *Chat* on the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:212
msgid "A user who is trying to enter a Group Meeting will enter the *waiting room*; here, the user remains until a Moderator grants the access; if the Meeting ends before entering, the user is notified that the meeting has ended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:217
msgid "On the bottom of the main area, the *Action Bar* allows to change or disable the devices, to share the screen, to change the mode of the call (see next section), or to leave the Meeting. Next to the red :bdg-warning:`leave meeting` button appears the duration of the meeting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:223
msgid "Leaving a meeting requires a confirmation click on the button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:227
msgid "Meeting modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:229
msgid "The right-hand side sidebar depends on the mode used during the meeting which can be one of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:235
msgid "Face to face mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:233
msgid "This is available only for a video call (i.e., between two participants) and the only interaction is to hide your video and show only the other participant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:244
msgid "Cinema mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:238
msgid "It is available only in video conferences. The sidebar shows a miniature of the participants. Only a few are shown in a vertical carousel, depending on the size of the browser's window, but you can scroll the carousel. By default, the main area shows the participant that is talking, but it is possible to force one participant to stick in the main area by pinning it (i.e., clicking the corresponding icon on the miniature)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:257
msgid "Grid mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:247
msgid "It is available only in video conferences. All the participants will be shown in the main area. When the number of participant is large and they can not be fit in a single window, it will be possible to scroll the grid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:252
msgid "It is also possible to pin one of the participants: in this case, the mode will be automatically switched to Cinema."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:255
msgid "To toggle between the Cinema and Grid modes use the button located between the screen share and leave buttons in the *Action Bar*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:260
msgid "Screen Sharing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:262
msgid "It is possible to share an entire screen or single windows. Depending on the browser used, it might be even possible to share only a tab of the browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_includes/_usage/wsc.rst:266
msgid "In video conferences, if someone (Alice) starts sharing the screen while someone else (Bob) is already sharing, the screen of Alice will replace Bob's. Bob's screen will remain shared, but other participants need to pin it to see it again in the main area."
msgstr ""
